# Project Overview

Stargazers is a modern CLI tool for analyzing GitHub repository stars and forks. The project follows a clean, modular structure:

- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Main documentation and usage guide
- [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) - Package configuration and dependencies
- [stargazers/](mdc:stargazers) - Main package directory containing core functionality
- [Makefile](mdc:Makefile) - makefile for common commands

## Key Features
- Fetch and analyze stargazers for GitHub repositories
- Analyze repository forkers
- Generate account-wide star trend analysis
- Export data to CSV files
- Terminal-based data visualization

## Main Commands
The CLI supports three main subcommands:
- `repos` - Analyze repository stargazers
- `forkers` - Analyze repository forkers  
- `account-trend` - Analyze star trends across all repos
